1
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:08,791
How impressive.

2
00:00:09,166 --> 00:00:11,875
They look incredibly sturdy.

3
00:00:12,291 --> 00:00:13,916
That's Lord Van for you.

4
00:00:14,041 --> 00:00:17,750
Thanks to your help,
we finished the ramparts in two weeks.

5
00:00:18,125 --> 00:00:20,125
In so little time?

6
00:00:20,666 --> 00:00:22,750
I know we helped out,

7
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:25,750
but I'm still shocked at what you can do.

8
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:29,458
Panamera's "ramparts"
are jutting out the most,

9
00:00:29,541 --> 00:00:32,166
but I'm not foolish enough
to say that out loud.

10
00:00:32,791 --> 00:00:38,583
We'll build more houses as more people
like merchants and adventurers move here.

11
00:00:39,041 --> 00:00:41,166
I'm positively envious of you.

12
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:43,875
It's been my dream to have my own land.

13
00:00:44,375 --> 00:00:48,250
In the next battle, I'll just have to earn
more glory than money can reward,

14
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:49,833
and ask for my own patch.

15
00:00:50,958 --> 00:00:52,083
By the way...

16
00:00:53,083 --> 00:00:54,416
What are those things?

17
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,125
Ballistae.

18
00:00:56,416 --> 00:01:00,375
I tried crafting larger versions of
the simple ballistae I'd made before.

19
00:01:00,708 --> 00:01:03,250
You made those, too, Lord Van?

20
00:01:03,583 --> 00:01:08,500
Yes. Top and bottom can fire separately,
so they can loose two bolts in a row.

21
00:01:09,750 --> 00:01:12,250
Khamsin, could you test-fire one for us?

22
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:13,500
Sure.

23
00:01:16,958 --> 00:01:18,250
Here I go.

24
00:01:26,458 --> 00:01:29,250
Yup, they came out quite well.

25
00:01:41,208 --> 00:01:46,291
EASYGOING TERRITORY DEFENSE
BY THE OPTIMISTIC LORD

26
00:01:46,375 --> 00:01:48,958
EPISODE 6: SLAYING A DANGEROUS
FOREST DRAGON WITH LARGE BALLISTAE

27
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:06,291
You have ballistae that powerful
atop your ramparts?

28
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,916
Yes, over a hundred of them.

29
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,166
A hundred?!

30
00:03:13,416 --> 00:03:15,875
Name your price. I'll buy one.

31
00:03:16,541 --> 00:03:19,458
I'm sorry, but these aren't for sale.

32
00:03:22,291 --> 00:03:25,750
Then, I'll owe you a favor, Lord Van.

33
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:29,208
In return, please let me
have one of these ballistae.

34
00:03:29,833 --> 00:03:31,166
I see.

35
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:33,583
Very well. I'll give you one.

36
00:03:33,708 --> 00:03:36,458
I'll call in that favor later.

37
00:03:36,541 --> 00:03:38,208
You have my gratitude.

38
00:03:38,291 --> 00:03:42,333
How will you transport it?
And what about the bolts to load into it?

39
00:03:42,625 --> 00:03:47,166
It does look rather heavy.
I'll arrange a carriage.

40
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:50,625
The bolts are made from iron,
so I can craft those on my end.

41
00:03:50,708 --> 00:03:51,958
Lady Panamera.

42
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:58,208
I think you should take at least
one or two of Lord Van's bolts.

43
00:03:58,291 --> 00:03:59,416
Why?

44
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,416
Take a look at this.

45
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:05,041
I've never seen a sword that shape before.

46
00:04:06,083 --> 00:04:10,916
Seems like it'd make heavy work
of foes with armor and shields.

47
00:04:11,416 --> 00:04:13,500
Got a sword you don't mind breaking?

48
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:16,208
This is my spare sword.

49
00:04:16,291 --> 00:04:17,791
If it breaks, so be it,

50
00:04:17,875 --> 00:04:20,833
but this beauty has seen me
through several battles.

51
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:23,750
I'd be impressed if you
even managed to chip it.

52
00:04:24,666 --> 00:04:26,708
Then, if I may...

53
00:04:30,625 --> 00:04:34,125
There was hardly an impact.
Did he just graze it?

54
00:04:38,041 --> 00:04:40,875
Very impressive.
It has an incredible edge, doesn't it?

55
00:04:40,958 --> 00:04:43,458
Lord Van made it, after all.

56
00:04:43,666 --> 00:04:46,208
What material is that sword made of?

57
00:04:46,291 --> 00:04:47,958
Ordinary iron.

58
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:50,208
That's impossible.

59
00:04:50,583 --> 00:04:53,458
Wait, you mean those bolts are also...

60
00:04:53,791 --> 00:04:56,458
I made them the same way
I did that sword.

61
00:04:56,500 --> 00:05:00,166
They pierce right through
two or three armored lizards.

62
00:05:00,416 --> 00:05:02,875
Pierce
through
armored lizards?

63
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:08,291
Lord Van, could I have some bolts
in addition to the ballista?

64
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:11,000
Of course. Pleasure doing business.

65
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:16,875
Khamsin, you have my gratitude. Thanks
to you, I'll also have powerful bolts.

66
00:05:16,958 --> 00:05:18,333
I'm happy for you.

67
00:05:19,458 --> 00:05:21,083
Everyone!

68
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,625
Run for your lives!

69
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:24,833
Ortho?

70
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:27,791
I'm sorry! We couldn't outrun it!

71
00:05:31,416 --> 00:05:33,708
- A dragon!
- It's huge!

72
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:36,458
We'll distract it to buy you some time!

73
00:05:36,541 --> 00:05:39,750
Use that to get everyone
back to the village!

74
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:42,166
They plan to be decoys for us?

75
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:44,625
But that puts Ortho's party in danger.

76
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:46,750
Should we fight back here?

77
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:49,791
But that could endanger the villagers.

78
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:51,375
I'll aid you.

79
00:05:51,791 --> 00:05:54,666
It's only a matter of time
before it heads this way.

80
00:05:56,916 --> 00:05:58,083
Ortho, this way!

81
00:05:58,166 --> 00:06:00,041
We'll shoot it down with the ballistae!

82
00:06:00,125 --> 00:06:01,666
Got it!

83
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:06,875
Today, we'll be fighting a forest dragon,
a mid-class dragon with no breath weapon.

84
00:06:07,958 --> 00:06:10,166
Someone escort Lady Arte
back to the village.

85
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:13,125
The rest of you hurry up onto
the ramparts. I'm right behind you.

86
00:06:13,208 --> 00:06:14,375
Yes, ma'am.

87
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:16,291
Lady Arte.

88
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:19,791
I'm sorry for exposing you
to such terrifying danger.

89
00:06:20,125 --> 00:06:22,916
I believe forest dragons
are very powerful foes.

90
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:26,875
But this time, we have
our enhanced ballistae.

91
00:06:27,125 --> 00:06:29,166
- We have Panamera as well.
- There's no time! Hurry!

92
00:06:30,166 --> 00:06:33,666
We might not be able to slay it,
but we won't be beaten.

93
00:06:33,916 --> 00:06:36,666
R-Right. Good luck.

94
00:06:38,708 --> 00:06:41,416
Till, escort Lady Arte.

95
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:44,750
Could you also summon Dee
and his men from the village?

96
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:45,958
Right.

97
00:06:47,916 --> 00:06:49,875
This is
too
scary!

98
00:06:49,958 --> 00:06:52,208
D-Don't close the gate!

99
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:54,375
We'll be right there!

100
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:57,000
Flying foes are trouble.

101
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,500
It won't be good
if it reaches the village.

102
00:07:00,541 --> 00:07:01,833
Ready the ballistae!

103
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:03,958
Be sure not to hit Ortho's party!

104
00:07:04,041 --> 00:07:05,166
Yes, sir!

105
00:07:05,250 --> 00:07:07,500
First, we'll ground it.

106
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:09,208
Aim for its wings!

107
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,583
Don't worry about me! Just go!

108
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,250
Come on. This way!

109
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:24,291
Damn it. It's not working!

110
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:27,291
Tsk. I don't have a choice!

111
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:30,375
I-It's coming!

112
00:07:31,291 --> 00:07:32,958
Sorry! Thank you!

113
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:36,833
Damn it! This is desperate now!

114
00:07:36,916 --> 00:07:39,500
Forget about me! All of you, run!

115
00:07:39,875 --> 00:07:42,208
All right! Everyone,
head for the ramparts!

116
00:07:42,291 --> 00:07:44,750
Huh?! Seriously, boss?!

117
00:07:45,083 --> 00:07:48,083
You're the fastest member of our party!

118
00:07:48,375 --> 00:07:51,166
I have faith you'll make it back alive!

119
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:53,291
Do you
really
mean that?!

120
00:07:53,375 --> 00:07:56,458
Everyone, let's never
forget Kusala's sacrifice!

121
00:07:56,541 --> 00:07:59,375
I'll get you back for this, boss!

122
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:02,375
Ballistae, once it is within range, fire!

123
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:04,791
Before it can get a taste of Kusala!

124
00:08:04,875 --> 00:08:08,083
Hey! Are you sure you're not
trying
to be mean, lord?!

125
00:08:10,625 --> 00:08:12,875
We can't hit it. What do we do?

126
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:16,041
I'm best suited to stopping its advance!

127
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:17,625
Panamera!

128
00:08:18,166 --> 00:08:20,291
Here comes my first strike!

129
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:24,666
I figured as much. Being valued
by the count at such a young age

130
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:28,333
and being made viscountess for
her exploits can only mean one thing.

131
00:08:29,875 --> 00:08:33,125
She's undoubtedly
a top-class elemental mage,

132
00:08:33,208 --> 00:08:36,416
and her aptitude will soon
become very obvious.

133
00:08:36,958 --> 00:08:39,000
Fire Javelin!

134
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:50,166
Incredible.

135
00:08:51,791 --> 00:08:52,875
It's not down yet.

136
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:58,500
I grew arrogant after
slaying those armored lizards.

137
00:08:58,833 --> 00:08:59,958
But this...

138
00:09:00,291 --> 00:09:01,916
is on a different level.

139
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:15,125
Fire all ballistae!

140
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:22,000
Good. We shot through its wings.

141
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,500
Second volley! Fire all bolts!

142
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:32,291
It read our second volley?

143
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:36,000
W-We're saved.

144
00:09:36,375 --> 00:09:39,750
W-We made it back alive somehow.

145
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:46,583
I-I won't forget how I was treated.

146
00:09:47,583 --> 00:09:49,750
I'm glad to see everyone's safe for now.

147
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:52,791
But if we stay here, we'll be in danger.

148
00:09:53,208 --> 00:09:55,125
I'd love to retreat to the village, but...

149
00:09:55,208 --> 00:09:57,041
I'll buy you time.

150
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,750
Fire Javelin!

151
00:10:02,083 --> 00:10:03,333
Not good enough?

152
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:14,250
So that's the true pinnacle of fire magic.

153
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:17,083
If she wasn't facing a dragon,

154
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:19,625
that power and versatility
would've been devastating.

155
00:10:19,916 --> 00:10:21,166
Lord Van!

156
00:10:23,708 --> 00:10:26,541
I'll head back first
and prepare to intercept it.

157
00:10:26,625 --> 00:10:29,333
Right. We'll be right behind you.

158
00:10:30,458 --> 00:10:33,291
Everyone! Let's take this chance
to flee to the village!

159
00:10:33,375 --> 00:10:34,583
Yes, sir.

160
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:57,291
It should've been seriously wounded.

161
00:10:59,291 --> 00:11:00,375
Esparda?

162
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:03,958
What are you doing? Hurry up and run.

163
00:11:05,833 --> 00:11:08,916
I won't run unless you're with me, too!

164
00:11:10,833 --> 00:11:12,583
That would be troublesome.

165
00:11:13,666 --> 00:11:16,750
Just this once, let me buy some time,
and then I'll head back.

166
00:11:34,875 --> 00:11:36,000
Good.

167
00:11:36,958 --> 00:11:39,500
That should buy us
a fair amount of time.

168
00:11:39,875 --> 00:11:43,083
He just casually dropped
one hell of a line.

169
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:44,875
That said...

170
00:11:46,041 --> 00:11:47,708
That's
way
too casual.

171
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:51,666
Don't
walk
away! Run!

172
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:55,000
Put some effort into it and
I'll get you that red wine you like!

173
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:59,125
Running is harsh on these old bones,
but I'll do my best.

174
00:11:59,208 --> 00:12:02,750
Lord Van, I'll stay by Sir Esparda's side.

175
00:12:02,958 --> 00:12:05,375
Go on ahead and take charge
of the village's defenses.

176
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:07,666
Right. Keep Esparda safe.

177
00:12:09,708 --> 00:12:11,791
But the village is quite a distance.

178
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:14,500
I'm running for all I'm worth,
but it's still so far away.

179
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:18,250
Ortho's party is almost fit to drop, too.

180
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:22,291
I need to buy more time
or the forest dragon will be on us again.

181
00:12:22,375 --> 00:12:23,625
Hey, boy!

182
00:12:24,125 --> 00:12:26,250
We're in position!

183
00:12:26,708 --> 00:12:28,000
Panamera!

184
00:12:28,208 --> 00:12:31,291
Mind if I call in that favor right now?

185
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:36,125
Not at all. So? What am I doing?

186
00:12:36,875 --> 00:12:39,041
When the forest dragon
reaches the ramparts,

187
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:42,208
use that magic you did earlier
to pin it down!

188
00:12:42,458 --> 00:12:45,750
Then, we'll hit it with a barrage
from the ballistae!

189
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:48,625
Good plan.

190
00:12:48,708 --> 00:12:52,916
Still, who would've thought my magic
would be used to merely pin down a foe?

191
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:57,041
Sorry about this! I'll share the dragon
meat with you, so please forgive me!

192
00:12:58,583 --> 00:13:00,000
Very well!

193
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:06,750
Okay, the meat is on the move.

194
00:13:07,291 --> 00:13:09,250
Ballistae, prepare to fire.

195
00:13:10,416 --> 00:13:13,583
I know it's scary, but be sure
to draw back far enough before firing.

196
00:13:13,666 --> 00:13:14,833
Right.

197
00:13:15,291 --> 00:13:17,708
If I could just buy a little more time...

198
00:13:18,083 --> 00:13:20,125
Leave it to me!

199
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:21,541
Dee?

200
00:13:22,416 --> 00:13:23,875
Sorry we're late.

201
00:13:23,958 --> 00:13:26,375
Deputy Commander, we can't keep up.

202
00:13:28,291 --> 00:13:30,291
Uh, will you three be okay?

203
00:13:30,375 --> 00:13:31,625
It won't be a problem!

204
00:13:31,708 --> 00:13:35,125
We have the weapons you made, after all!

205
00:13:58,708 --> 00:14:01,375
Esparda! Khamsin! Hurry!

206
00:14:03,625 --> 00:14:05,541
- Retreat!
- Yes, sir!

207
00:14:11,958 --> 00:14:13,500
We've drawn it in close enough.

208
00:14:13,875 --> 00:14:14,916
Panamera!

209
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,458
Right!

210
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:22,083
Flare Blast!

211
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:35,250
- Now!
- Fire all ballistae!

212
00:15:10,291 --> 00:15:11,708
We did it.

213
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:19,833
We won! Let's raise our voices in victory!

214
00:15:26,291 --> 00:15:28,333
Are you all right, Lord Van?

215
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:30,416
You aren't hurt, are you?

216
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:33,333
No, I'm fine, thanks to everyone.

217
00:15:35,583 --> 00:15:37,875
Lady Arte. So this is where you were.

218
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:39,583
Lady Panamera.

219
00:15:40,041 --> 00:15:42,875
Don't worry. I'm unharmed, too.

220
00:15:43,125 --> 00:15:44,416
Thank goodness.

221
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:47,750
You gave good commands, boy.

222
00:15:48,166 --> 00:15:50,333
Congratulations on slaying a dragon.

223
00:15:50,416 --> 00:15:52,833
We cut it very close, though.

224
00:15:53,166 --> 00:15:56,416
Regular villages would've
been wiped off the map.

225
00:15:56,791 --> 00:15:58,916
Heroes like your butler, Esparda,

226
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:04,375
and Dee, the man who beheaded that dragon
in one stroke, aren't very common.

227
00:16:05,125 --> 00:16:07,250
I'm proud to call them my friends.

228
00:16:07,708 --> 00:16:11,625
Not to mention, you had those ballistae
with their ridiculous force.

229
00:16:12,625 --> 00:16:15,875
I can't believe they were able
to pierce a dragon's scales.

230
00:16:15,958 --> 00:16:18,875
Still, I'll need to
upgrade them even more.

231
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:23,041
They need to be capable of
firing ten successive bolts at least.

232
00:16:23,125 --> 00:16:25,875
I feel like you just said
something terrifying.

233
00:16:26,291 --> 00:16:27,250
Well, anyway...

234
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:30,375
For now, we need to host
a dragon-slaying ceremony.

235
00:16:30,458 --> 00:16:31,541
A ceremony?

236
00:16:32,208 --> 00:16:36,833
The most distinguished in battle
receives the title of "Dragonslayer."

237
00:16:36,916 --> 00:16:38,250
That's Sir Dee.

238
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:39,458
Huh?

239
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:42,958
Dee's being made a Dragonslayer?

240
00:16:47,125 --> 00:16:50,750
Today, we have slain the lord
of the forest: a forest dragon.

241
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:55,375
We are here to honor the deeds
of those who contributed the most.

242
00:16:56,208 --> 00:17:01,500
Now, over to the head of House Cayenne,
Viscountess Panamera Carrera Cayenne.

243
00:17:01,916 --> 00:17:08,166
The forest dragon you slew today would've
wiped most villages and towns off the map,

244
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:11,458
and most fortress cities
wouldn't have fared much better.

245
00:17:12,541 --> 00:17:16,916
Yet this small village not only survived,
but suffered absolutely no casualties.

246
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:21,041
Even the total damage was a small portion
of the ramparts and two ballistae.

247
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:25,416
I will now call out the names
of those who contributed most.

248
00:17:25,875 --> 00:17:29,666
First up is Dee, deputy commander
of House Fertio's Chivalric Order.

249
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:33,166
He beheaded the forest dragon
in one fell stroke,

250
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:36,541
dealing the decisive blow in the battle.

251
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:41,708
Next is the exceptional
elemental mage, Esparda.

252
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:47,000
Words cannot describe his talent for magic
that let him pin the dragon down.

253
00:17:48,166 --> 00:17:52,625
Last up is House Fertio's fourth son,
Van Nei Fertio.

254
00:17:52,708 --> 00:17:54,750
Yeah!

255
00:17:54,833 --> 00:17:56,333
W-Wow.

256
00:17:56,833 --> 00:18:00,708
His knowledge, decisiveness, and genius
are rare in a boy of eight,

257
00:18:00,791 --> 00:18:03,333
and he has made
unprecedented use of his magic

258
00:18:03,416 --> 00:18:06,583
to greatly strengthen
this village's defenses in a short time.

259
00:18:07,083 --> 00:18:09,250
In the battle with the forest dragon,

260
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:12,583
he took charge and led our men
to victory as lord of this land.

261
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:14,625
Lord Van!

262
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:17,083
Lord Van!

263
00:18:17,166 --> 00:18:22,500
I've met people of every status
on my rise from lowly knight.

264
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:24,916
Yet has there ever been a man like him?

265
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:31,125
I was born into a long line
of knights in the royal capital.

266
00:18:31,375 --> 00:18:33,875
But when my aptitude
for magic was known,

267
00:18:34,125 --> 00:18:38,166
I was quickly handed to the county
that offered me the best conditions.

268
00:18:39,125 --> 00:18:41,541
My grueling training
made me wish for death,

269
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:46,000
and I sacrificed sleep to study
in my quest to become a squad commander.

270
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,041
My feats were recognized,

271
00:18:48,125 --> 00:18:51,291
and I was made commander of
the county's chivalric order at 16.

272
00:18:51,375 --> 00:18:56,583
After that, I fought in several battles,
earning enough glory to be made a noble.

273
00:18:57,041 --> 00:18:59,625
His Majesty was delighted
with my success,

274
00:18:59,708 --> 00:19:03,708
so six very short years later,
I was given the title of viscountess.

275
00:19:05,708 --> 00:19:09,541
Then one day, I was summoned
by Count Ferdinatto.

276
00:19:10,125 --> 00:19:14,500
He told me he wished to wed his youngest
daughter to the lord of some remote land.

277
00:19:14,958 --> 00:19:18,250
I-It's been a long time, Father.

278
00:19:18,708 --> 00:19:20,125
This is her.

279
00:19:20,625 --> 00:19:21,750
I see.

280
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:28,000
Still, wouldn't a letter of introduction
suffice to someone with no title?

281
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:30,333
In most circumstances, yes.

282
00:19:30,416 --> 00:19:34,375
Well, even if anything happens,
you're only dealing with a young boy.

283
00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:35,625
It won't be an issue.

284
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,083
Understood.

285
00:19:38,666 --> 00:19:42,291
Well, depending on what he's like,
I can just bring her back.

286
00:19:44,083 --> 00:19:47,166
Hey, Lady Arte On Ferdinatto.

287
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:50,666
I'm Viscountess Panamera
Carrera Cayenne.

288
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:59,416
Did you hear? If he's talented,
he'll become your fiancé.

289
00:20:00,166 --> 00:20:04,250
But if he's incompetent, I'll reject him
for you, so you don't need to worry.

290
00:20:04,875 --> 00:20:08,125
I-I'm unwanted?

291
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:12,000
That's why they're forcing me
out of my home, isn't it?

292
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:15,708
That's not why at all.

293
00:20:17,458 --> 00:20:22,375
I don't know if you know this, but all
of your siblings have fiancés already.

294
00:20:22,458 --> 00:20:23,750
You're the last one.

295
00:20:26,708 --> 00:20:28,250
I hope he's a nice boy.

296
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:34,541
When I left my parents long ago,
I was filled with anxiety.

297
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:39,416
So perhaps I projected myself
onto Lady Arte.

298
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:42,916
But my fears were all for nothing.

299
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,500
After meeting this boy,

300
00:20:44,583 --> 00:20:49,875
the timid Lady Arte began taking
the initiative to push things forward.

301
00:20:51,791 --> 00:20:57,000
This boy is a breath of fresh air
in a way I've never experienced before.

302
00:21:00,583 --> 00:21:03,916
I, Viscountess Panamera Carrera Cayenne,

303
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:08,333
hereby vow to forge an equal alliance
with Van Nei Ferdinatto.

304
00:21:08,875 --> 00:21:10,333
An alliance?

305
00:21:10,583 --> 00:21:13,750
Up until now, you haven't had any support
from the marquis, correct?

306
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:17,375
But if you ally yourselves with me,
I can promise you support.

307
00:21:18,041 --> 00:21:22,333
You won't have to worry about Count
Ferdinatto's knights invading, either.

308
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:26,625
True, if I forge an alliance,
I'll replace enemies with allies.

309
00:21:26,916 --> 00:21:30,375
It'll also help us financially,
so it's a win-win.

310
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:34,625
You managed to develop this village
in such a short time.

311
00:21:35,083 --> 00:21:38,166
Don't you think you should set
your sights even higher?

312
00:21:38,625 --> 00:21:40,416
Forge an equal alliance with me,

313
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:46,458
and the nobles of this kingdom will soon
learn that Lord Van is my sworn friend.

314
00:21:46,916 --> 00:21:49,166
So? Will you accept?

315
00:21:50,041 --> 00:21:53,916
With my father cutting me off and
few connections among the nobility,

316
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,916
this is a great opportunity
I may never get again.

317
00:21:58,666 --> 00:22:01,625
Thank you for the offer.
May our friendship hold strong.

318
00:23:38,625 --> 00:23:43,750
NEXT EPISODE: EARNEST MERCHANTS
AND RECEIVING A PROUD TITLE
